memgraph-mage-full is a metapackage. It contains no files of its own;
installing it pulls in `memgraph-mage` and `memgraph-mage-debuginfo` at
matching versions in one step, equivalent to:

    apt install memgraph-mage memgraph-mage-debuginfo

Use this when you want the MAGE query modules with symbolicated stack
traces ready to go, without having to remember the companion package
name.

Removal note: `apt remove memgraph-mage-full` does not by itself
uninstall `memgraph-mage` or `memgraph-mage-debuginfo`, but those
packages are flagged as automatically installed. They will be removed
by the next `apt autoremove` unless you mark them manual:

    apt-mark manual memgraph-mage memgraph-mage-debuginfo
